.SH DESCRIPTION
This package provides a container class for generating \fIpdf\fR documents\&.
.SH COORDINATES
All coordinates and distances can be expressed with or without a unit\&. See
\fBUNITS\fR for valid units\&.
When the page is configured with \fB-orient\fR set to false, origin is in
the bottom left corner\&. With \fB-orient\fR true (the default), origin is in the top left
corner\&.
Origin is displaced to account for margins, i\&.e\&. if margins are 100,
the user coordinate (0,0) corresponds to (100,100) on the paper\&.
Page option \fB-orient\fR can also affect the anchor point for things like
images\&.
.SH UNITS
Any coordinates and distances can be expressed with or without an explicit
unit\&.  If no unit is given, the default unit for the document is used\&.
A unit may be one of
\fBmm\fR (millimeter),
\fBm\fR (millimeter),
\fBcm\fR (centimeter),
\fBc\fR (centimeter),
\fBp\fR (points) or
\fBi\fR (inches)\&.
Commands returning coordinates or distances always return a double value
in the document's default unit\&.
.SH "PUBLIC API"
.SS "PACKAGE COMMANDS"
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::new\fR \fIobjectName\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This command creates a new pdf4tcl object with an associated Tcl
command whose name is \fIobjectName\fR\&. This \fIobject\fR command is
explained in full detail in the sections \fBOBJECT COMMAND\fR
and \fBOBJECT METHODS\fR\&. The object command will be created
under the current namespace if the \fIobjectName\fR is not fully
qualified, and in the specified namespace otherwise\&.
If \fIobjectName\fR is %AUTO% a name will generated\&.
The return value is the newly created object's name\&.
.sp
The options and their values coming after the name of the object are
used to set the initial configuration of the object\&.
See \fBOBJECT CONFIGURATION\fR\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::getPaperSize\fR \fIpaper\fR
This call returns the size of a named paper type, e\&.g\&. "a4"\&.
Paper names are case insensitive\&.
The argument \fIpaper\fR may also be a two element list
with values as accepted by \fB::pdf4tcl::getPoints\fR\&.
The return value is a list with width and height in points\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::getPaperSizeList\fR
This call returns the list of known paper types\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::getPoints\fR \fIval\fR
This call translates a measurement to points (1/72 inch)\&.
The format of \fIval\fR is '\fInum\fR ?\fIunit\fR?' where
\fInum\fR is a valid integer or double\&. See \fBUNITS\fR for valid
\fIunit\fRs\&.  If no \fIunit\fR is given, the value is interpreted
as points\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::loadBaseTrueTypeFont\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIttf_file_name\fR
This call loads a TTF font from file to be used by any pdf4tcl objects\&.
The \fIbasefontname\fR is used to reference this font\&.
To use this base font in documents, a font with some encoding must be
created from it using \fBcreateFont\fR, \fBcreateFontSpecEnc\fR, or
\fBcreateFontSpecCID\fR\&.
.sp
Only TrueType outline fonts (TTF) are supported\&. The following font types
are detected and rejected with a descriptive error:
.RS
.IP \(bu
Color bitmap fonts with CBDT/CBLC tables (e\&.g\&. "\fINotoColorEmoji\&.ttf\fR")
.IP \(bu
Apple bitmap fonts with sbix table (macOS system emoji)
.IP \(bu
Layered color vector fonts with COLR/CPAL tables (e\&.g\&. Segoe UI Emoji on Windows)
.IP \(bu
OpenType fonts with PostScript outlines (OTTO magic, CFF-based)
.RE
.sp
For emoji and symbol coverage, use a vector outline font such as
"\fINotoEmoji-Regular\&.ttf\fR" (\fIhttps://fonts\&.google\&.com/noto/specimen/Noto+Emoji\fR)
or "\fISymbola\&.ttf\fR" (\fIhttps://dn-works\&.com/ufas/\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::createBaseTrueTypeFont\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIttf_data\fR
This call creates a base font from TTF binary data\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::loadBaseType1Font\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIAFM_file_name\fR \fIPFB_file_name\fR
This call loads a Type1 font from two files (\&.afm and \&.pfb) to be used by
any pdf4tcl objects\&. The \fIbasefontname\fR is used to reference this font\&.
To use this base font in documents, a font with some encoding must be
created from it using \fBcreateFont\fR or \fBcreateFontSpecEnc\fR\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::createBaseType1Font\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIAFM_data\fR \fIPFB_data\fR
This call creates a base font from AFM text and PFB binary data\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::createFont\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIfontname\fR \fIencoding_name\fR
This call creates a font that can be used in documents from a base font\&. The given encoding
defines the (up to) 256 unicode characters that can be drawn when \fIfontname\fR is selected\&.
To use more characters, multiple fonts need to be created and selected based on what needs to be written\&.
.CS


pdf4tcl::loadBaseTrueTypeFont BaseArial "arial\&.ttf"
pdf4tcl::createFont BaseArial MyArial cp1251
pdf4tcl::loadBaseType1Font BaseType1 "a010013l\&.afm" "a010013l\&.pfb"
pdf4tcl::createFont BaseType1 MyType1 cp1251
pdf4tcl::new mypdf -paper a4 -compress 0
mypdf startPage
mypdf setFont 10 MyArial
set txt "\\u042D\\u0442\\u043E \\u0442\\u0435\\u043A\\u0441\\u0442 \\u043D\\u0430 \\u0440\\u0443\\u0441\\u0441\\u043A\\u043E\\u043C\\
         \\u044F\\u0437\\u044B\\u043A\\u0435\&. This is text in Russian\&."
mypdf text $txt -bg #CACACA -x 50 -y 100
mypdf setFont 10 MyType1
mypdf text $txt -x 50 -y 200
mypdf write -file fonts\&.pdf
mypdf destroy

.CE
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::createFontSpecEnc\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIfontname\fR \fIsubset\fR
This call creates a font that can be used in documents from a base font\&.
The \fIsubset\fR must be a list of (up to 256) unicode values which are the characters that can be
drawn when \fIfontname\fR is selected\&.
.CS


pdf4tcl::loadBaseTrueTypeFont BaseArial "arial\&.ttf"
# Subset is a list of unicodes:
for {set f 0} {$f < 128} {incr f} {lappend subset $f}
lappend subset [expr 0xB2] [expr 0x3B2]
pdf4tcl::createFontSpecEnc BaseArial MyArial $subset
pdf4tcl::new mypdf -paper a4
mypdf startPage
mypdf setFont 16 MyArial
set txt "sin\\u00B2\\u03B2 + cos\\u00B2\\u03B2 = 1"
mypdf text $txt -x 50 -y 100
mypdf write -file specenc\&.pdf
mypdf destroy

.CE
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::createFontSpecCID\fR \fIbasefontname\fR \fIfontname\fR
This call creates a Unicode-capable CID font (CIDFontType2 with Identity-H encoding)
from a previously loaded TrueType base font\&. Unlike \fBcreateFont\fR and \fBcreateFontSpecEnc\fR,
which are limited to 256 characters per font instance, a CID font supports any Unicode
character covered by the underlying TTF file\&. This includes Latin Extended, Greek, Cyrillic,
CJK ideographs, and other scripts\&. The full TTF binary is embedded in the PDF\&.
.sp
Characters in the Supplementary Multilingual Plane (SMP, U+10000 and above) are
supported\&. They are encoded as UTF-16BE surrogate pairs in the ToUnicode CMap,
as required by the PDF specification (ISO 32000, §9\&.10\&.3)\&.
This enables correct text extraction and copy-paste from PDF viewers for characters
such as mathematical alphanumerics (U+1D400), musical symbols (U+1D100),
or emoji from vector outline fonts (U+1F300 and above)\&.
.CS


pdf4tcl::loadBaseTrueTypeFont DejaVuSans "/usr/share/fonts/truetype/dejavu/DejaVuSans\&.ttf"
pdf4tcl::createFontSpecCID DejaVuSans myCIDFont

pdf4tcl::new mypdf -paper a4
mypdf startPage
mypdf setFont 14 myCIDFont
mypdf text "Latin: Hello World" -x 50 -y 750
mypdf text "Extended: \\u00e4\\u00f6\\u00fc\\u00df" -x 50 -y 720
mypdf text "Greek: \\u0391\\u03b2\\u03b3\\u03b4" -x 50 -y 690
mypdf text "Cyrillic: \\u041f\\u0440\\u0438\\u0432\\u0435\\u0442" -x 50 -y 660
mypdf endPage
mypdf write -file unicode\&.pdf
mypdf destroy

.CE
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::getFonts\fR
This call returns the list of known font names, i\&.e\&. those accepted in a call
to \fBsetFont\fR\&.
This includes the default fonts and fonts created by e\&.g\&.
\fB::pdf4tcl::createFont\fR\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::rgb2Cmyk\fR \fIrgb\fR
This call translates an RGB color value to a CMYK color value\&.
It is used internally if \fB-cmyk\fR was set at object creation to
translate colors\&.
You can redefine this procedure to provide your own translation\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::cmyk2Rgb\fR \fIcmyk\fR
This call translates a CMYK color value to an RGB color value\&.
It is used internally to translate colors\&.
You can redefine this procedure to provide your own translation\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::catPdf\fR \fIinfile\fR ?\fIinfile \&.\&.\&.\fR? \fIoutfile\fR
This call concatenates PDF files into one\&.
Currently the implementation limits the PDFs a lot since not all details
are taken care of yet\&. Straightforward ones like those created with pdf4tcl
or ps2pdf should work mostly ok\&.
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::getForms\fR \fIinfile\fR
This call extracts form data from a PDF file\&.
The return value is a dictionary with id/info pairs\&.
The id is the one set with \fI-id\fR to \fBaddForm\fR, if the PDF
was generated with pdf4tcl\&.
The info is a dictionary with the following fields:
.RS
.TP
\fBtype\fR
Field type\&.
.TP
\fBvalue\fR
Form value\&.
.TP
\fBflags\fR
Value of form flags field\&.
.TP
\fBdefault\fR
Default value, if any\&.
.RE
.TP
\fB::pdf4tcl::exportForms\fR \fIinfile\fR \fIoutfile\fR ?\fIoptions\fR?
Export form field data from a filled PDF as FDF or XFDF (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
Returns the number of exported fields\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-format\fR \fIfdf|xfdf\fR
Output format\&. \fBfdf\fR (default): Forms Data Format (ISO 32000 SS12\&.7\&.7),
a compact text format supported by most PDF viewers\&.
\fBxfdf\fR: XML Forms Data Format (ISO 32000 SS12\&.7\&.8), human-readable XML\&.
.TP
\fB-password\fR \fIstring\fR
Password for encrypted PDFs\&.
.RE
.CS


# Export as FDF
pdf4tcl::exportForms filled\&.pdf data\&.fdf

# Export as XFDF
pdf4tcl::exportForms filled\&.pdf data\&.xfdf -format xfdf

.CE
.PP
.SS "OBJECT COMMAND"
All commands created by \fB::pdf4tcl::new\fR have the following
general form and may be used to invoke various operations on their
pdf object\&.
.TP
\fBobjectName\fR \fBmethod\fR ?\fIarg arg \&.\&.\&.\fR?
The method \fBmethod\fR and its \fIarg\fR'uments determine the exact
behavior of the command\&. See section \fBOBJECT METHODS\fR for
the detailed specifications\&.
.PP
.SS "OBJECT METHODS"
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBconfigure\fR
The method returns a list of all known options and their current
values when called without any arguments\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBconfigure\fR \fIoption\fR
The method behaves like the method \fBcget\fR when called with a
single argument and returns the value of the option specified by said
argument\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBconfigure\fR \fB-option\fR \fIvalue\fR\&.\&.\&.
The method reconfigures the specified \fBoption\fRs of the object,
setting them to the associated \fIvalue\fRs, when called with an even
number of arguments, at least two\&.
.sp
The legal options are described in the section
\fBOBJECT CONFIGURATION\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBcget\fR \fB-option\fR
This method expects a legal configuration option as argument and will
return the current value of that option for the object the method was
invoked for\&.
.sp
The legal configuration options are described in section
\fBOBJECT CONFIGURATION\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBdestroy\fR
This method destroys the object it is invoked for\&.
If the \fB-file\fR option was given at object creation,
the output file will be finished and closed\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBstartPage\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method starts a new page in the document\&. The page will have the
default page settings for the document unless overridden by \fIoption\fR\&.
See \fBPAGE CONFIGURATION\fR for page settings\&.
This will end any ongoing page\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBendPage\fR
This method ends a page in the document\&.  It is normally not needed since
it is implied by e\&.g\&. \fBstartPage\fR and \fBfinish\fR\&.  However,
if the document is built page by page in e\&.g\&. an event driven environment
it can be good to call \fBendPage\fR explicitly to have all the page's
work finished before reentering the event loop\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBstartXObject\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method starts a new XObject in the document\&.  An XObject is a reusable
drawing object and behaves just like a page where you can draw any graphics\&.
An XObject must be created between pages and this method will end any ongoing
page\&. The return value is an id that can be used with \fBputImage\fR to draw
it on the current page or with some forms\&.
All page settings (\fBPAGE CONFIGURATION\fR) are
valid when creating an XObject\&. Default options are
\fB-paper\fR = {100p 100p}, \fB-landscape\fR = 0,
\fB-orient\fR = document default, \fB-margin\fR= 0\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-noimage\fR \fIbool\fR
If this is set the XObject is not added to the image resource set and cannot
be used with putImage, only in forms\&. The XObject also gets access to resources
which is needed to use e\&.g\&. fonts within the XObject\&. This behaviour has shown
to be PDF reader dependent, and it is currently not known if this can be
made to work better\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBendXObject\fR
This method ends an XObject definition\&. It works just like \fBendPage\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBfinish\fR
This method ends the document\&.
This will do \fBendPage\fR if needed\&.
If the \fB-file\fR option was given at object creation,
the output file will be finished and closed\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBget\fR
This method returns the generated pdf\&.
This will do \fBendPage\fR and \fBfinish\fR if needed\&.
If the \fB-file\fR option was given at object creation, nothing is returned\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBwrite\fR ?\fI-file filename\fR? ?\fI-dryrun bool\fR?
This method writes the generated pdf to the given \fIfilename\fR\&.
If no \fIfilename\fR is given, it is written to stdout\&.
This will do \fBendPage\fR and \fBfinish\fR if needed\&.
If the \fB-file\fR option was given at object creation, an empty file
is created\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-file\fR \fIfilename\fR
Write PDF to the given file\&.
.TP
\fB-dryrun\fR \fIbool\fR
If true, return the PDF data as a string without writing to a file and without
modifying the document state\&. Useful for previewing or testing the output\&.
Default is false\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddForm\fR \fItype\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add an interactive form field at the given position and size\&.
Coordinates are in the document's current unit\&.
Supported types are \fItext\fR, \fIpassword\fR, \fIcheckbutton\fR
(alias \fIcheckbox\fR), \fIcombobox\fR, \fIlistbox\fR,
\fIradiobutton\fR, \fIpushbutton\fR, and \fIsignature\fR\&.
.RS
.TP
\fICommon options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-id\fR \fIstring\fR
Unique field ID (alphanumeric)\&. If omitted, one is generated
automatically: \fI${type}form${n}\fR for most types,
\fI${group}_${value}\fR for radiobuttons,
\fISignature${n}\fR for signatures\&.
.TP
\fB-init\fR \fIvalue\fR
Initial value\&. For \fItext\fR/\fIpassword\fR a string,
for \fIcheckbutton\fR a boolean, for \fIcombobox\fR/\fIlistbox\fR
an item from \fI-options\fR, for \fIradiobutton\fR a boolean
selecting this button\&.
.TP
\fB-readonly\fR \fIboolean\fR
If true, the field is read-only (PDF Ff bit 1)\&. Default \fB0\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-required\fR \fIboolean\fR
If true, the field is marked as required (PDF Ff bit 2)\&. Default \fB0\fR\&.
Not valid for \fIpushbutton\fR or \fIsignature\fR\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIText / Password options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-multiline\fR \fIboolean\fR
Enable multi-line editing (text only)\&. Default \fB0\fR\&.
.RE
.TP
\fICheckbutton options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-on\fR \fIxobjectId\fR
Custom appearance XObject for the checked state\&.
Created with \fBstartXObject\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-off\fR \fIxobjectId\fR
Custom appearance XObject for the unchecked state\&.
.RE
.TP
\fICombobox / Listbox options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-options\fR \fIlist\fR
List of selectable items\&. Required for \fIcombobox\fR and \fIlistbox\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-editable\fR \fIboolean\fR
Allow typing custom values (combobox only)\&. Default \fB0\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-sort\fR \fIboolean\fR
Sort the option list\&. Default \fB0\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-multiselect\fR \fIboolean\fR
Allow selecting multiple items (listbox only)\&. Default \fB0\fR\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIRadiobutton options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-group\fR \fIstring\fR
Group name (required, alphanumeric)\&. All buttons sharing the same
group name form a mutually exclusive set\&.
.TP
\fB-value\fR \fIstring\fR
Value for this button (required, alphanumeric)\&. Used as the
PDF appearance state name\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIPushbutton options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-action\fR \fItype\fR
Action type: \fBreset\fR (clear all fields), \fBurl\fR (open URL),
or \fBsubmit\fR (submit form data to URL)\&.
.TP
\fB-url\fR \fIstring\fR
Target URL\&. Required when \fI-action\fR is \fBurl\fR or \fBsubmit\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-caption\fR \fIstring\fR
Button label text\&. Either \fI-action\fR or \fI-caption\fR (or both)
must be given\&.
.RE
.TP
\fISignature options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-label\fR \fIstring\fR
Placeholder text displayed on the signature line\&.
Default \fBSignature\fR\&. Only valid for \fIsignature\fR fields\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIAccessibility and tab order options\fR
.RS
.TP
\fB-tooltip\fR \fIstring\fR
Tooltip text written as PDF \fB/TU\fR (Tooltip User) entry\&.
Displayed by PDF readers on hover and read aloud by screen readers
(PDF/UA)\&. Valid for all field types\&.
.TP
\fB-tabindex\fR \fIinteger\fR
Tab order index written as PDF \fB/TI\fR entry\&. Must be a
non-negative integer\&. Used to define the logical keyboard tab order
within the AcroForm\&. Valid for all field types\&.
.RE
.RE
.IP
All fields generate their own appearance streams; the
\fBNeedAppearances\fR flag is never set, ensuring compatibility
with digital signature workflows\&.
Radiobutton groups are finalized at document write time as a
parent field with \fB/Kids\fR entries\&.
.PP
.SS "OBJECT METHODS, PAGE"
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetDrawableArea\fR
This method returns the size of the available area on the page,
after removing margins\&.  The return value is a list of width and height,
in the document's default unit\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBcanvas\fR \fIpath\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draws the contents of the canvas widget \fIpath\fR on the current page\&.
The return value is the bounding box in pdf page coordinates of the area covered\&.
Option \fI-bbox\fR gives the area of the canvas to be drawn\&. Default is
the entire contents, i\&.e\&. the result of $path bbox all\&.
Options \fI-x\fR, \fI-y\fR, \fI-width\fR and \fI-height\fR defines
an area on the page where to place the contents\&. Default area starts at origin,
stretching over the drawable area of the page\&.
Option \fI-sticky\fR defines how to place the contents within the area\&.
The area is always filled in one direction, preserving aspect ratio, unless
\fI-sticky\fR defines that the other direction should be filled too\&.  Default
\fI-sticky\fR is \fInw\fR\&.
If option \fI-bg\fR is true, a background is drawn in the canvas' background
color\&.  Otherwise only objects are drawn\&.  Default is false\&.
Option \fI-fontmap\fR gives a dictionary mapping from Tk font names to PDF font names\&.
Option \fI-textscale\fR overrides the automatic downsizing made for tk::canvas text items that are deemed too large\&. If \fI-textscale\fR is larger than 1, all text items are reduced in size by that factor\&.
.sp
Fonts:
.sp
If no font mapping is given, fonts for text items are limited to PDF's
builtins, i\&.e\&. Helvetica, Times and Courier\&. A guess is made to chose which
one to use to get a reasonable display on the page\&.
.sp
An element in a font mapping must exactly match the -font option in the
text item\&. The corresponding mapping value is a PDF font family, e\&.g\&. one
created by \fBpdf4tcl::createFont\fR, possibly followed by a size\&.
It is recommended to use named fonts
in Tk to control the font mapping in detail\&.
.sp
Limitations:
.sp
Option \fB-splinesteps\fR for lines/polygons is not applicable: PDF uses
exact cubic Bezier curves (\fBCanvasBezier\fR), which are mathematically
equivalent to any number of spline steps\&. The visual result is equal to or
better than Tk's screen rendering\&.
.sp
\fIStipple:\fR
Both offset forms are supported: \fBx,y\fR (absolute pixel offset) and
\fB#x,y\fR (bitmap-relative -- aligns bitmap pixel (x,y) with canvas
origin)\&. Empty offset (no adjustment) is handled correctly\&. Minor visual
differences from on-screen rendering may remain due to pattern scaling\&.
.sp
\fIWidget classes supported:\fR
\fBtk::canvas\fR (class \fBCanvas\fR) -- all standard item types:
rectangle, oval, line, polygon, arc, text, image, bitmap, window\&.
.sp
\fBtkpath\fR (\fB::tkp::canvas\fR, class \fBPathCanvas\fR) -- tkpath
item types: pimage, ptext, pline, polyline, ppolygon, prect, circle,
ellipse, path, group\&. Handled via \fBitempdf\fR delegation (C-level)\&.
.sp
\fBtko::path\fR (class \fBtko::path\fR) -- tko::path item types:
image, text, line, polyline, polygon, rect, circle, ellipse, path, group,
window\&. Handled via \fBitempdf\fR delegation\&.
.sp
\fIWindow items (tk::canvas):\fR
The embedded widget must be visible on-screen when the canvas is exported\&.
Package \fBImg\fR with \fB-format window\fR support is required to
capture the widget as a raster image\&. If \fBImg\fR is not available or
the widget is unmapped, a solid black rectangle is drawn in its place\&.
.sp
\fIWindow items (tko::path):\fR
The item is silently skipped -- no crash, no error message (fix in 0\&.9\&.4\&.24,
BUG-C1)\&. All other items on the same \fBtko::path\fR are exported correctly\&.
Raster capture of embedded widgets is not supported for \fBtko::path\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBmetadata\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method sets metadata fields for this document\&.  Supported field options are
\fI-author\fR, \fI-creator\fR, \fI-keywords\fR, \fI-producer\fR, \fI-subject\fR,
\fI-title\fR, \fI-creationdate\fR and \fI-moddate\fR\&.
Multiple keywords should be passed as a comma-separated string,
e\&.g\&. \fI-keywords "tcl,pdf,document"\fR\&.
For \fI-creationdate\fR and \fI-moddate\fR a \fBclock seconds\fR value is expected\&.
A value of \fB0\fR uses the current date and time\&.
Unknown option names cause an error\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBbookmarkAdd\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add a bookmark on the current page\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-title\fR \fItext\fR
Set the text of the bookmark\&.
.TP
\fB-level\fR \fIlevel\fR
Set the level of the bookmark\&. Default is 0\&.
.TP
\fB-closed\fR \fIboolean\fR
Select if the bookmark is closed by default\&. Default is false, i\&.e\&. not closed\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBembedFile\fR \fIfilename\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method embeds a file into the PDF stream\&. File data is considered binary\&. Returns an id that can be used in subsequent calls to \fBattachFile\fR\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-id\fR \fIid\fR
Explicitly select an id for the file\&. The \fIid\fR must be unique within the document\&.
.TP
\fB-contents\fR \fIdata\fR
Provides the file contents instead of reading the actual file\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBattachFile\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR \fIfid\fR \fIdescription\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method adds a file annotation to the current page\&. The location of the file annotation is given by the coordinates \fIx\fR, \fIy\fR, \fIwidth\fR, \fIheight\fR\&. The annotation is rendered by default as a paperclip icon, which allows the extraction of the attached file\&. An \fIfid\fR from a previous call to \fBembedFile\fR must be set as well as a \fIdescription\fR, which is shown by the PDF viewer upon activating the annotation\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-icon\fR \fIicon\fR
Controls the appearance of the attachment\&. Valid values are Paperclip, Tag, Graph, or PushPin\&. Default value is Paperclip\&.
.RE
.CS


set fid [$pdfobject embedFile "data\&.txt" -contents "This should be stored in the file\&."]
$pdfobject attachFile 0 0 100 100 $fid "This is the description"

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddEmbeddedFile\fR \fIfilename\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method embeds a file silently into the PDF document via the Catalog
\fB/Names\fR / \fB/EmbeddedFiles\fR NameTree (ISO 32000 SS7\&.11\&.4)\&.
No visible annotation is created on any page\&.
This is the correct mechanism for electronic invoice attachments
(ZUGFeRD, Factur-X) and other document-level file attachments\&.
.sp
\fIfilename\fR is used as the display name stored in the PDF
(\fB/F\fR and \fB/UF\fR entries of the FileSpec dictionary)\&.
When \fB-contents\fR is not given, the file is read from disk using
\fIfilename\fR as path; in that case the basename is used as the PDF name\&.
.sp
\fIPDF/A-1 restriction:\fR embedded files are forbidden by
ISO 19005-1 SS6\&.1\&.7\&.  Calling this method when \fB-pdfa\fR is
set to \fB1b\fR raises an error\&.  PDF/A-2b and PDF/A-3b allow
embedded files\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-contents\fR \fIdata\fR
Raw binary content of the file\&.  If omitted, the file is read from
disk using \fIfilename\fR as path\&.
.TP
\fB-mimetype\fR \fItype\fR
MIME type string, e\&.g\&. \fBapplication/xml\fR\&.
Written as \fB/Subtype\fR in the EmbeddedFile stream dictionary\&.
.TP
\fB-description\fR \fItext\fR
Human-readable description stored as \fB/Desc\fR in the FileSpec
dictionary\&.
.TP
\fB-afrelationship\fR \fIrel\fR
PDF/A-3 \fB/AFRelationship\fR entry\&.  Valid values are
\fBAlternative\fR, \fBData\fR, \fBSource\fR,
\fBSupplement\fR, and \fBUnspecified\fR\&.
.RE
.CS


# ZUGFeRD / Factur-X pattern
set xmlData [read [open "factur-x\&.xml" rb]]
$pdfobject addEmbeddedFile "factur-x\&.xml"  -contents $xmlData  -mimetype "application/xml"  -description "Factur-X invoice"  -afrelationship Alternative

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBhyperlinkAdd\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR \fIurl\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
This method adds a URI hyperlink annotation to the current page\&. The clickable
area is defined by \fIx\fR, \fIy\fR, \fIwidth\fR and \fIheight\fR\&. The
\fIurl\fR argument must be a valid URI string (e\&.g\&. \fBhttps://www\&.example\&.com\fR)\&.
By default the annotation has no visible border\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-borderwidth\fR \fIn\fR
Width of the annotation border in points\&. Use \fB0\fR for an invisible border
(default: \fB0\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-bordercolor\fR \fIcolor\fR
Color of the annotation border\&. Accepts any color format supported by pdf4tcl
(default: \fB{0 0 1}\fR, blue)\&.
.TP
\fB-borderradius\fR \fIn\fR
Corner radius of the annotation border in points (default: \fB0\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-borderdash\fR \fIon off\fR
Dash pattern of the border as a list of two numbers \fIon\fR and \fIoff\fR in
points\&. An empty list produces a solid border (default: \fB\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-highlight\fR \fImode\fR
Visual effect when the user clicks the annotation\&. Valid values are \fBN\fR
(None), \fBI\fR (Invert, default), \fBO\fR (Outline), and \fBP\fR (Push)\&.
.RE
.CS


# Invisible link
$pdfobject hyperlinkAdd 50 100 200 20 "https://sourceforge\&.net/p/pdf4tcl"

# Link with visible blue border
$pdfobject hyperlinkAdd 50 130 200 20 "https://github\&.com/gregnix/pdf4tcl"  -borderwidth 1 -bordercolor {0 0 1}

# Dashed border, rounded corners
$pdfobject hyperlinkAdd 50 160 200 20 "https://www\&.tcl\&.tk"  -borderwidth 1 -bordercolor {0 0\&.6 0} -borderdash {5 3} -borderradius 4

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotNote\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add a \fB/Text\fR sticky note annotation (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
The annotation appears as a small icon; clicking it opens a popup window\&.
\fINote:\fR Popup behaviour varies between PDF viewers -- some keep the popup
open, others do not show a close button\&. For consistent cross-viewer display
use \fBaddAnnotFreeText\fR instead\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-content\fR \fIstring\fR
Note text shown in the popup\&.
.TP
\fB-author\fR \fIstring\fR
Author name shown in the popup header\&.
.TP
\fB-subject\fR \fIstring\fR
Subject line\&.
.TP
\fB-icon\fR \fIname\fR
Icon type: \fBNote\fR (default), \fBComment\fR,
\fBKey\fR, \fBHelp\fR, \fBNewParagraph\fR, \fBParagraph\fR, \fBInsert\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-color\fR \fIcolor\fR
Background color (default: \fB1 1 0\fR = yellow)\&.
.TP
\fB-open\fR \fIbool\fR
Show popup open by default (default: \fB0\fR)\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotFreeText\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR \fItext\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add a \fB/FreeText\fR annotation -- a visible text box directly on the page (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
No click required; always visible in all viewers\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-fontsize\fR \fIn\fR
Font size in points (default: \fB10\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-color\fR \fIcolor\fR
Text color (default: \fB0 0 0\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-bgcolor\fR \fIcolor\fR
Background fill color (default: \fB1 1 0\&.8\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-borderwidth\fR \fIn\fR
Border width in points (default: \fB1\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-align\fR \fIn\fR
Text alignment: \fB0\fR=left (default), \fB1\fR=center, \fB2\fR=right\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotHighlight\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotUnderline\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotStrikeOut\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Text markup annotations (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&. The rectangle defines the text area to mark\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-color\fR \fIcolor\fR
Markup color\&. Defaults: yellow for Highlight,
black for Underline, red for StrikeOut\&.
.TP
\fB-content\fR \fIstring\fR
Optional comment text\&.
.TP
\fB-author\fR \fIstring\fR
Author name\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotStamp\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add a \fB/Stamp\fR annotation -- a rubber stamp visible on the page (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-name\fR \fIname\fR
Predefined stamp name (default: \fBDraft\fR)\&.
Valid names: \fBApproved\fR, \fBConfidential\fR, \fBDraft\fR, \fBExperimental\fR,
\fBExpired\fR, \fBFinal\fR, \fBForPublicRelease\fR, \fBNotApproved\fR,
\fBNotForPublicRelease\fR, \fBSold\fR, \fBTopSecret\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-color\fR \fIcolor\fR
Stamp color (default: \fB1 0 0\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-content\fR \fIstring\fR
Optional popup content\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddAnnotLine\fR \fIx1\fR \fIy1\fR \fIx2\fR \fIy2\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add a \fB/Line\fR annotation with optional arrowheads (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-color\fR \fIcolor\fR
Line color (default: \fB0 0 0\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-width\fR \fIn\fR
Line width in points (default: \fB1\fR)\&.
.TP
\fB-startend\fR \fIlist\fR
Two-element list of arrowhead styles for
start and end of the line (default: \fBNone None\fR)\&.
Valid styles: \fBNone\fR, \fBOpenArrow\fR, \fBClosedArrow\fR, \fBSquare\fR,
\fBCircle\fR, \fBDiamond\fR, \fBButt\fR, \fBSlash\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-content\fR \fIstring\fR
Optional popup content\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBviewerPreferences\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Set viewer preference flags in the PDF catalog\&. These control how a PDF viewer
displays the document when it is opened\&. Options can be combined freely\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-pagelayout\fR \fIlayout\fR
Set the page layout on open\&. Valid values: \fBSinglePage\fR, \fBOneColumn\fR,
\fBTwoColumnLeft\fR, \fBTwoColumnRight\fR, \fBTwoPageLeft\fR, \fBTwoPageRight\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-pagemode\fR \fImode\fR
Set the page mode on open\&. Valid values: \fBUseNone\fR, \fBUseOutlines\fR,
\fBUseThumbs\fR, \fBFullScreen\fR, \fBUseOC\fR, \fBUseAttachments\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-hidetoolbar\fR \fIbool\fR
Hide the viewer toolbar when the document is open (default false)\&.
.TP
\fB-hidemenubar\fR \fIbool\fR
Hide the viewer menu bar (default false)\&.
.TP
\fB-hidewindowui\fR \fIbool\fR
Hide viewer interface elements (default false)\&.
.TP
\fB-fitwindow\fR \fIbool\fR
Resize the document window to fit the first page (default false)\&.
.TP
\fB-centerwindow\fR \fIbool\fR
Center the document window on the screen (default false)\&.
.TP
\fB-displaydoctitle\fR \fIbool\fR
Display the document title from metadata instead of the file name (default false)\&.
.TP
\fB-nonfullscreenpagemode\fR \fImode\fR
Page mode when leaving full-screen mode\&. Valid values: \fBUseNone\fR,
\fBUseOutlines\fR, \fBUseThumbs\fR, \fBUseOC\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-direction\fR \fIdir\fR
Reading order\&. Valid values: \fBL2R\fR (default) or \fBR2L\fR (right-to-left)\&.
.TP
\fB-printscaling\fR \fIscale\fR
Default print scaling\&. Valid values: \fBAppDefault\fR or \fBNone\fR\&.
.TP
\fB-duplex\fR \fImode\fR
Paper handling when printing\&. Valid values: \fBNone\fR, \fBSimplex\fR,
\fBDuplexFlipShortEdge\fR, \fBDuplexFlipLongEdge\fR\&.
.RE
.CS


$pdfobject viewerPreferences -pagemode FullScreen -hidetoolbar 1
$pdfobject viewerPreferences -pagelayout TwoColumnLeft -direction L2R

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBpageLabel\fR \fIpageIndex\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Define a page label range starting at the given zero-based \fIpageIndex\fR\&.
PDF page labels allow viewers to display custom page numbers (e\&.g\&. roman numerals
for a preface, decimal numbers for the main body)\&. Multiple ranges can be defined\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-style\fR \fIstyle\fR
Numbering style\&. Valid values: \fBD\fR (decimal: 1 2 3), \fBr\fR (roman lowercase: i ii iii),
\fBR\fR (roman uppercase: I II III), \fBa\fR (alpha lowercase: a b c),
\fBA\fR (alpha uppercase: A B C), or empty string (prefix only, no number)\&.
.TP
\fB-prefix\fR \fIstring\fR
Label prefix prepended to each page number (e\&.g\&. \fBApp-\fR produces App-1, App-2\&.\&.\&.)\&.
.TP
\fB-start\fR \fIinteger\fR
Start value for the numbering in this range\&. Must be a positive integer\&. Default is 1\&.
.RE
.CS


# Preface pages: i, ii, iii\&.\&.\&.
$pdfobject pageLabel 0 -style r

# Main body pages: 1, 2, 3\&.\&.\&.
$pdfobject pageLabel 4 -style D -start 1

# Appendix with prefix
$pdfobject pageLabel 20 -style A -prefix "App-"

.CE
.PP
.SS "OBJECT METHODS, TEXT"
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetFont\fR \fIsize\fR ?\fIfontname\fR?
This method sets the font used by text drawing routines\&. If \fIfontname\fR
is not provided, the previously set \fIfontname\fR is kept\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetStringWidth\fR \fIstr\fR ?\fIoptions\fR?
This method returns the width of \fIstr\fR in the current unit\&.
Options (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+):
.RS
.TP
\fB-font\fR \fIfontName\fR
Use \fIfontName\fR instead of the current font\&.
.TP
\fB-size\fR \fIfontSize\fR
Use \fIfontSize\fR instead of the current font size\&.
.TP
\fB-internal\fR \fIbool\fR
Return width in points instead of current unit\&.
.RE
.IP
Without options the method behaves as before\&.
If no font has been set and \fB-font\fR is not given, an error is raised\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetCharWidth\fR \fIchar\fR
This method returns the width of a character under the current font\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBinPage\fR
Returns \fB1\fR if a page is currently open, \fB0\fR otherwise\&.
Useful for library code managing page state without accessing internals\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBcurrentPage\fR
Returns the current page number (1-based)\&.
Returns \fB0\fR before the first \fBstartPage\fR call\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBpageCount\fR
Returns the number of completed pages (\fBendPage\fR called)\&.
A currently open page is not counted until \fBendPage\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetTextPosition\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR
Set coordinate for next text command\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBmoveTextPosition\fR \fIdx\fR \fIdy\fR
Increment position by \fIdx\fR, \fIdy\fR for the next text command\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetTextPosition\fR
This method returns the current text coordinate\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBnewLine\fR ?\fIspacing\fR?
Moves text coordinate down and resets x to where the latest
\fBsetTextPosition\fR was\&. The number of lines to move down can
be set by \fIspacing\fR\&. This may be any real number, including negative,
and defaults to the value set by \fBsetLineSpacing\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetLineSpacing\fR \fIspacing\fR
Set the default line spacing used be e\&.g\&. \fBnewLine\fR\&.  Initially
the spacing is 1\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetLineSpacing\fR
Get the current default line spacing factor (a dimensionless multiplier)\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetLineHeight\fR
Get the actual vertical distance advanced by \fBnewLine\fR in the document's
current unit\&. This is \fIfont_size\fR times the line spacing factor\&. Use this to
calculate bounding boxes around multi-line text blocks\&. Requires a font to be set\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBtext\fR \fIstr\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw text at the position defined by setTextPosition using the font defined by
setFont\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-align\fR \fIleft|right|center\fR   (default left)
.TP
\fB-angle\fR \fIdegrees\fR   (default 0) - Orient string at the specified angle\&.
.TP
\fB-xangle\fR \fIdegrees\fR   (default 0)
.TP
\fB-yangle\fR \fIdegrees\fR   (default 0) - Apply x or y shear to the text\&.
.TP
\fB-x\fR \fIx\fR   (default 0)
.TP
\fB-y\fR \fIy\fR   (default 0) - Allow the text to be positioned without setTextPosition\&.
.TP
\fB-bg\fR \fIbool|color\fR   (default 0)
.TP
\fB-background\fR \fIbool|color\fR
.TP
\fB-fill\fR \fIbool|color\fR
Any of \fB-bg\fR, \fB-background\fR or \fB-fill\fR cause the text to be drawn
on a filled background\&. If a boolean true is given, the background color is taken from
\fBsetBgColor\fR\&. Alternatively, a color value in any format accepted by pdf4tcl
can be given directly (e\&.g\&. \fB{1 0 0}\fR for red)\&. All three options are aliases\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBdrawTextBox\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR \fIstr\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw the text string \fIstr\fR wrapping at blanks and tabs so that it fits within the box defined
by \fIx\fR, \fIy\fR, \fIwidth\fR and \fIheight\fR\&. An embedded newline in \fIstr\fR causes
a new line in the output\&. If \fIstr\fR is too long to fit in the specified box, it is truncated and the unused remainder is returned\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-align\fR \fIleft|right|center|justify\fR
Specifies the justification\&. If not given, the text is left justified\&.
.TP
\fB-linesvar\fR \fIvar\fR
Gives the name of a variable which will be set to the number of lines written\&.
.TP
\fB-newyvar\fR \fIvar\fR
Gives the name of a variable which will be set to the Y position after
the last rendered line, in the current unit (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
Allows the caller to continue drawing below the text box:
.CS


$pdf drawTextBox $x $y $w $h $text -newyvar nextY
$pdf line $x $nextY [expr {$x+$w}] $nextY

.CE
.TP
\fB-dryrun\fR \fIbool\fR
If true, no changes will be made to the PDF document\&. The return
value and \fB-linesvar\fR gives information of what would happen
with the given text\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetFontMetric\fR \fImetric\fR
Get information about current font\&. The available \fImetric\fRs are
\fBascend\fR, \fBdescend\fR, \fBfixed\fR, \fBbboxb\fR,
\fBbboxt\fR and \fBheight\fR\&.
.RS
.TP
\fBascend\fR
Top of typical glyph, displacement from anchor point\&. Typically a positive number since it is above the anchor point\&.
.TP
\fBdescend\fR
Bottom of typical glyph, displacement from anchor point\&. Typically a negative number since it is below the anchor point\&.
.TP
\fBfixed\fR
Boolean which is true if this is a fixed width font\&.
.TP
\fBbboxb\fR
Bottom of Bounding Box, displacement from anchor point\&. Typically a negative number since it is below the anchor point\&.
.TP
\fBbboxt\fR
Top of Bounding Box, displacement from anchor point\&. Typically a positive number since it is above the anchor point\&.
.TP
\fBheight\fR
Height of font's Bounding Box\&.
.RE
.PP
.SS "OBJECT METHODS, IMAGES"
A limited set of image formats are directly understood by pdf4tcl,
currently some JPEG, some PNG, and some TIFF formats\&.
To use unsupported formats, use Tk and the Img
package to load and dump images to raw format which can be fed to
\fBputRawImage\fR and \fBaddRawImage\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBputImage\fR \fIid\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Put an image on the current page\&. The image must have been added previously by
\fBaddImage\fR or \fBaddRawImage\fR\&. The \fIid\fR is the one returned
from the add command\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-angle\fR \fIdegrees\fR
Rotate image \fIdegrees\fR counterclockwise around the anchor point\&.
Default is 0\&.
.TP
\fB-anchor\fR \fIanchor\fR
Set the anchor point (nw, n, ne etc\&.) of the image\&.
Coordinates \fIx\fR and \fIy\fR places the anchor point, and any rotation is around the anchor point\&.
Default is nw if \fB-orient\fR is true, otherwise se\&.
.TP
\fB-height\fR \fIheight\fR
Set the height of the image\&.  Default height is one point per pixel\&.  If \fIwidth\fR is set but not \fIheight\fR,
the height is selected to preserve the aspect ratio of the image\&.
.TP
\fB-width\fR \fIwidth\fR
Set the width of the image\&.  Default width is one point per pixel\&.
If \fIheight\fR is set but not \fIwidth\fR, the width is selected to
preserve the aspect ratio of the image\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBputRawImage\fR \fIdata\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Put an image on the current page\&. Works like \fBputImage\fR except that the raw image data is given directly\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-compress\fR \fIboolean\fR
Raw data will be zlib compressed if this option is set to true\&.
Default value is the document's \fB-compress\fR setting\&.
.RE
.CS


  image create photo img1 -file image\&.gif
  set imgdata [img1 data]
  mypdf putRawImage $imgdata 60 20 -height 40

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddImage\fR \fIfilename\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add an image to the document\&. Returns an id that can be used in subsequent
calls to \fBputImage\fR\&. Supported formats are PNG, JPEG and TIFF\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-id\fR \fIid\fR
Explicitly select an id for the image\&. The \fIid\fR must be unique within the document\&.
.TP
\fB-type\fR \fIname\fR
Override automatic type detection based on file extension\&.
Valid values are \fBpng\fR, \fBjpg\fR (or \fBjpeg\fR), \fBtif\fR (or \fBtiff\fR)\&.
Set the image type\&.  This can usually be deduced from the file name, this
option helps when that is not possible\&.  This can be either "png", "jpeg",
or "tiff"\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddRawImage\fR \fIdata\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Add an image to the document\&. Works like \fBaddImage\fR except that the raw image data is given directly\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-compress\fR \fIboolean\fR
Raw data will be zlib compressed if this option is set to true\&.
Default value is the document's \fB-compress\fR setting\&.
.RE
.CS


  image create photo img1 -file image\&.gif
  set imgdata [img1 data]
  set id [mypdf addRawImage $imgdata]
  mypdf putImage $id 20 60 -width 100

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetImageHeight\fR \fIid\fR
This method returns the height of the image identified by \fIid\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetImageSize\fR \fIid\fR
This method returns the size of the image identified by \fIid\fR\&.  The
return value is a list of width and height\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetImageWidth\fR \fIid\fR
This method returns the width of the image identified by \fIid\fR\&.
.PP
.SS "OBJECT METHODS, COLORS"
Colors can be expressed in various formats\&. First, as a three element list
of values in the range 0\&.0 to 1\&.0\&. Second, in the format #XXXXXX where
the Xes are two hexadecimal digits per color value\&.  Third, if Tk is available,
any color accepted by winfo rgb is accepted\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetBgColor\fR \fIred\fR \fIgreen\fR \fIblue\fR
Sets the background color for text operations where -bg is true\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetBgColor\fR \fIc\fR \fIm\fR \fIy\fR \fIk\fR
Alternative calling form, to set color in CMYK color space\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetFillColor\fR \fIred\fR \fIgreen\fR \fIblue\fR
Sets the fill color for graphics operations, and the foreground color for
text operations\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetFillColor\fR \fIc\fR \fIm\fR \fIy\fR \fIk\fR
Alternative calling form, to set color in CMYK color space\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetStrokeColor\fR \fIred\fR \fIgreen\fR \fIblue\fR
Sets the stroke color for graphics operations\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetStrokeColor\fR \fIc\fR \fIm\fR \fIy\fR \fIk\fR
Alternative calling form, to set color in CMYK color space\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetAlpha\fR \fIvalue\fR
Sets the opacity for both fill and stroke operations\&.
\fIvalue\fR must be a number between 0\&.0 (fully transparent) and 1\&.0 (fully
opaque)\&. Values outside this range are clamped\&. The default is 1\&.0\&.
Internally this creates a PDF ExtGState object with \fB/ca\fR (fill alpha)
and \fB/CA\fR (stroke alpha)\&. Identical alpha values are cached and reuse
the same ExtGState object\&. The alpha state is saved and restored by
\fBgsave\fR / \fBgrestore\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetAlpha\fR \fIvalue\fR \fB-fill\fR
Sets fill opacity only, leaving stroke opacity unchanged\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetAlpha\fR \fIvalue\fR \fB-stroke\fR
Sets stroke opacity only, leaving fill opacity unchanged\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetAlpha\fR \fIfillValue\fR \fIstrokeValue\fR
Sets fill and stroke opacity independently in a single call\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetAlpha\fR
Returns the current opacity values as a two-element list
\fIfillAlpha strokeAlpha\fR\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetBlendMode\fR \fImode\fR
Sets the PDF blend mode for subsequent graphics and text operations\&.
\fImode\fR must be one of: \fBNormal\fR, \fBMultiply\fR, \fBScreen\fR,
\fBOverlay\fR, \fBDarken\fR, \fBLighten\fR, \fBColorDodge\fR,
\fBColorBurn\fR, \fBHardLight\fR, \fBSoftLight\fR, \fBDifference\fR,
\fBExclusion\fR, \fBHue\fR, \fBSaturation\fR, \fBColor\fR,
\fBLuminosity\fR\&.
Use \fBNormal\fR to reset to the default\&. Internally this creates a PDF
ExtGState object combining \fB/BM\fR with the current alpha values; objects
are cached per mode and alpha combination\&. The PDF version is raised to 1\&.4
automatically\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetBlendMode\fR
Returns the currently active blend mode string (default: \fBNormal\fR)\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBlinearGradient\fR \fIx1\fR \fIy1\fR \fIx2\fR \fIy2\fR \fIcolor1\fR \fIcolor2\fR ?\fIoptions\fR?
Paints a linear (axial) gradient from (\fIx1\fR,\fIy1\fR) to
(\fIx2\fR,\fIy2\fR)\&. \fIcolor1\fR is the colour at the start point,
\fIcolor2\fR at the end point\&. Both colours can be specified as an RGB triple
\fI{r g b}\fR (values 0\&.0–1\&.0), a named colour (\fBred\fR, \fBgreen\fR,
\fBblue\fR, \fBwhite\fR, \fBblack\fR, \fByellow\fR, \fBcyan\fR,
\fBmagenta\fR) or a CSS hex string \fI#rrggbb\fR\&.
.sp
Options:
.RS
.TP
\fB-extend\fR \fI{bool bool}\fR
Whether to extend the gradient beyond
the start (\fIbool1\fR) and end (\fIbool2\fR) coordinates\&. Default: \fB1 1\fR\&.
.RE
.sp
The gradient is painted using PDF ShadingType 2 + FunctionType 2 and
registered in the page \fB/Shading\fR resource dictionary\&.
Clip the drawing area first (e\&.g\&. \fBclip\fR or \fBgsave\fR/\fBgrestore\fR)
to constrain the fill\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBradialGradient\fR \fIcx1\fR \fIcy1\fR \fIr1\fR \fIcx2\fR \fIcy2\fR \fIr2\fR \fIcolor1\fR \fIcolor2\fR ?\fIoptions\fR?
Paints a radial gradient between two circles\&. The first circle is centred at
(\fIcx1\fR,\fIcy1\fR) with radius \fIr1\fR; the second at (\fIcx2\fR,\fIcy2\fR)
with radius \fIr2\fR\&. \fIcolor1\fR applies to the first circle,
\fIcolor2\fR to the second\&. Colour formats are the same as for
\fBlinearGradient\fR\&.
.sp
Options: same \fB-extend\fR option as \fBlinearGradient\fR\&.
.sp
Uses PDF ShadingType 3 + FunctionType 2\&.
.PP
.SS "OBJECT METHODS, GRAPHICS"
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetLineWidth\fR \fIwidth\fR
Sets the width for subsequent line drawing\&.
Line width must be a non-negative number\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetLineDash\fR ?\fIon off\fR\&.\&.\&.? ?\fIoffset\fR?
Sets the dash pattern for subsequent line drawing\&.
Offset and any elements in the dash pattern must be non-negative numbers\&.
\fIon off\fR is a series of pairs of numbers which define a
dash pattern\&. The 1st, 3rd \&.\&.\&. numbers give units to paint,
the 2nd, 4th \&.\&.\&. numbers specify unpainted gaps\&. When all numbers have
been used, the pattern is re-started from the beginning\&.
An optional last argument sets the dash offset, which defaults to 0\&.
Calling \fBsetLineDash\fR with no arguments resets the dash pattern
to a solid line\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBsetLineStyle\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIargs\fR
Sets the width and dash pattern for subsequent line drawing\&.
Line width and any elements in the dash pattern must be non-negative numbers\&.
\fIargs\fR is a series of numbers (not a tcl list) which define a
dash pattern\&. The 1st, 3rd \&.\&.\&. numbers give units to paint,
the 2nd, 4th \&.\&.\&. numbers specify unpainted gaps\&. When all numbers have
been used, the pattern is re-started from the beginning\&.
This method do not support offsetting the pattern, see \fBsetLineDash\fR
for a more complete method\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBline\fR \fIx1\fR \fIy1\fR \fIx2\fR \fIy2\fR
Draws a line from \fIx1,\fR \fIy1\fR to \fIx2,\fR \fIy2\fR
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBcurve\fR \fIx1\fR \fIy1\fR \fIx2\fR \fIy2\fR \fIx3\fR \fIy3\fR ?\fIx4 y4\fR?
If \fIx4,\fR \fIy4\fR are present, draws a cubic bezier from \fIx1,\fR
\fIy1\fR to \fIx4,\fR \fIy4\fR with control points \fIx2,\fR \fIy2\fR and
\fIx3,\fR \fIy3\fR\&. Otherwise draws a quadratic bezier from \fIx1,\fR
\fIy1\fR to \fIx3,\fR \fIy3\fR, with control point \fIx2,\fR
\fIy2\fR
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBpolygon\fR ?\fIx y\fR\&.\&.\&.? ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw a polygon\&. There must be at least 3 points\&.
The polygon is closed back to the first coordinate unless \fI-closed\fR is false in which case a poly-line is drawn\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-filled\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 0)
Fill the polygon\&.
.TP
\fB-stroke\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Draw an outline of the polygon\&.
.TP
\fB-closed\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Close polygon\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBcircle\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIradius\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw a circle at the given center coordinates\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-filled\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 0)
Fill the circle\&.
.TP
\fB-stroke\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Draw an outline of the circle\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBoval\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIradiusx\fR \fIradiusy\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw an oval at the given center coordinates\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-filled\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 0)
Fill the oval\&.
.TP
\fB-stroke\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Draw an outline of the oval\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBarc\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIradiusx\fR \fIradiusy\fR \fIphi\fR \fIextend\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw an arc, following the given oval\&. The arc starts at angle \fIphi\fR, given in degrees starting in the "east" direction, counting counter clockwise\&. The arc extends \fIextend\fR degrees\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-filled\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 0)
Fill the arc\&.
.TP
\fB-stroke\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Draw an outline of the arc\&.
.TP
\fB-style\fR \fIarc|pieslice|chord\fR   (default \fIarc\fR)
Defines the style of the arc\&. An \fIarc\fR draws the perimeter of the arc and is never filled\&. A \fIpieslice\fR closes the arc with lines to the center of the oval\&. A \fIchord\fR closes the arc directly\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBarrow\fR \fIx1\fR \fIy1\fR \fIx2\fR \fIy2\fR \fIsize\fR ?\fIangle\fR?
Draw an arrow\&. Default \fIangle\fR is 20 degrees\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBrectangle\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw a rectangle\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-filled\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 0)
Fill the rectangle\&.
.TP
\fB-stroke\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Draw an outline of the rectangle\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBroundedRect\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR ?\fIoption value\fR\&.\&.\&.?
Draw a rectangle with rounded corners (Bezier approximation)\&.
.RS
.TP
\fB-radius\fR \fIvalue\fR   (default 5)
Corner radius in the document's current unit\&. Automatically clamped
to half the shorter side\&.
.TP
\fB-filled\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 0)
Fill the rectangle\&.
.TP
\fB-stroke\fR \fIbool\fR   (default 1)
Draw an outline of the rectangle\&.
.RE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBclip\fR \fIx\fR \fIy\fR \fIwidth\fR \fIheight\fR
Create a clip region\&. To cancel a clip region you must restore a graphic context that was saved before\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgsave\fR
Save graphic/text context\&. (I\&.e\&. insert a raw PDF "q" command)\&.
This saves the settings of at least these calls: \fBclip\fR, \fBsetBgColor\fR, \fBsetFillColor\fR, \fBsetStrokeColor\fR, \fBsetAlpha\fR, \fBsetLineStyle\fR, \fBsetLineWidth\fR, \fBsetLineDash\fR, \fBsetFont\fR, and \fBsetLineSpacing\fR\&.
Each call to \fBgsave\fR should be followed by a later call to \fBgrestore\fR in the same page\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgrestore\fR
Restore graphic/text context\&. (I\&.e\&. insert a raw PDF "Q" command)\&.
Restores all saved state including the raw-coordinate mode set by
\fBtranslate\fR, \fBrotate\fR, \fBscale\fR, or \fBtransform\fR\&.
After \fBgrestore\fR, drawing commands return to user-coordinate mode
(orient + margin active)\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBtransform\fR \fIa\fR \fIb\fR \fIc\fR \fId\fR \fIe\fR \fIf\fR
Apply a PDF transformation matrix (\fBcm\fR operator) to the current
graphics state\&. Use with \fBgsave\fR/\fBgrestore\fR\&.
.sp
After this call, drawing commands (\fBline\fR, \fBrectangle\fR etc\&.)
work in raw-coordinate mode: y points upward, no margin, no orient flip\&.
Text commands (\fBtext\fR) use absolute \fBTm\fR positioning and are
\fInot\fR affected by transformation matrices\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBtranslate\fR \fItx\fR \fIty\fR
Shift the coordinate origin by \fItx\fR/\fIty\fR in the current unit,
respecting orient and margins\&. Equivalent to
\fBtransform\fR \fB1 0 0 1 tx ty\fR (after coordinate conversion)\&.
.sp
\fIRaw-coordinate note:\fR after \fBtranslate\fR, drawing commands
work in raw PDF space (y upward)\&. A \fBrectangle\fR \fB0 0 w h\fR
draws \fIh\fR points \fIupward\fR from the new origin\&. To place the
bottom edge of a rectangle at user-y \fIy\fR, pass
\fB[expr {$y + $h}]\fR as the \fIty\fR argument:
.CS


$pdf gsave
$pdf translate $x [expr {$y + $h}]  ;# bottom edge at user-y
$pdf rectangle 0 0 $w $h
$pdf grestore

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBrotate\fR \fIdegrees\fR
Rotate the coordinate system clockwise by \fIdegrees\fR\&.
Typical use: \fBtranslate\fR to the pivot point, then \fBrotate\fR\&.
Like \fBtranslate\fR, switches to raw-coordinate mode\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBscale\fR \fIsx\fR \fIsy\fR
Scale the coordinate system (\fB1\&.0\fR = unchanged)\&.
Like \fBtranslate\fR, switches to raw-coordinate mode\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBgetPageSize\fR
Return the full page dimensions as \fB{width height}\fR in the
current unit (set via \fB-unit\fR at creation time)\&.
For A4 with \fB-unit mm\fR: approximately \fB210\&.0 297\&.0\fR\&.
For A4 with \fB-unit p\fR: approximately \fB595\&.0 842\&.0\fR
(pdf4tcl rounds MediaBox to integer points)\&.
Complements \fBgetDrawableArea\fR which excludes margins\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddEmbeddedFile\fR \fIfilename\fR ?\fIoptions\fR?
Embed a file in the PDF\&.
When \fB-pdfa 3b\fR is active the FileSpec OID is automatically
added to the document-level \fB/AF\fR array in the Catalog
(ISO 19005-3 SS6\&.2\&.11\&.4)\&.
.sp
Options: \fB-contents\fR, \fB-mimetype\fR, \fB-description\fR,
\fB-afrelationship\fR (Alternative|Data|Source|Supplement|Unspecified)\&.
.sp
\fINote:\fR Embedded files are forbidden in PDF/A-1 (ISO 19005-1 SS6\&.1\&.7)\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBaddLayer\fR \fIname\fR ?\fB-visible bool\fR?
Add an Optional Content Group (OCG / layer) to the document\&.
Returns a layer ID for use with \fBbeginLayer\fR\&.
.sp
\fIname\fR is the visible label shown in the viewer's layer panel\&.
\fB-visible\fR controls default visibility (1 = shown, 0 = hidden, default: 1)\&.
Use cases: debug grids (\fB-visible 0\fR), letterhead variants,
watermarks (\fB-visible 0\fR)\&.
.sp
\fINote:\fR \fBaddLayer\fR must be called before \fBfinish\fR\&.
All layers are shared across all pages of the document\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBbeginLayer\fR \fIlayerId\fR
Open an Optional Content Group block\&. All drawing commands until
\fBendLayer\fR belong to this layer\&.
\fIlayerId\fR is the OID returned by \fBaddLayer\fR\&.
Inserts a \fBBDC\fR operator into the content stream\&.
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fBendLayer\fR
Close the current Optional Content Group block\&.
Inserts an \fBEMC\fR operator into the content stream\&.
.CS


set lGrid [$pdf addLayer "Debug-Raster" -visible 0]
set lKopf [$pdf addLayer "Briefkopf"   -visible 1]

$pdf beginLayer $lGrid
  $pdf setStrokeColor 0\&.9 0\&.9 0\&.9
  for {set x 0} {$x <= 595} {incr x 50} { $pdf line $x 0 $x 842 }
$pdf endLayer

$pdf beginLayer $lKopf
  $pdf text "Musterfirma GmbH" -x 40 -y 28
$pdf endLayer

.CE
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fB_WriteXrefTable\fR \fIidHash\fR \fIencdict_oid\fR \fImetadata_oid\fR
.TP
\fIobjectName\fR \fB_WriteXrefStream\fR \fIidHash\fR \fIencdict_oid\fR \fImetadata_oid\fR
Internal methods for writing the cross-reference section\&.
\fB_WriteXrefTable\fR writes the classic text-based xref table and trailer dict\&.
\fB_WriteXrefStream\fR writes a binary XRef stream object (PDF 1\&.5+,
required for PDF/A-2b+)\&. The XRef stream object contains all trailer entries
(\fB/Root\fR, \fB/Info\fR, \fB/ID\fR) eliminating the need for a
separate trailer dictionary\&.
.sp
Selection is automatic: \fB-pdfa 2b\fR uses \fB_WriteXrefStream\fR,
all other modes use \fB_WriteXrefTable\fR\&.
.PP
.SS "OBJECT CONFIGURATION"
All pdf4tcl objects understand the options from \fBPAGE CONFIGURATION\fR,
which defines default page settings when used with a pdf4tcl object\&.
The objects also understand the following configuration options:
.TP
\fB-cmyk\fR \fIboolean\fR
If true, pdf4tcl will try to generate the document in CMYK color space\&.
See \fB::pdf4tcl::rgb2Cmyk\fR for a way to control color translation\&.
Default value is false\&.
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-compress\fR \fIboolean\fR
Pages will be zlib compressed if this option is set to true\&.
Default value is true\&.
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-file\fR \fIfilename\fR
Continuously write pdf to \fIfilename\fR instead of storing it
in memory\&.
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-unit\fR \fIdefaultunit\fR
Defines default unit for coordinates and distances\&.  Any value given without
a unit is interpreted using this unit\&.
See \fBUNITS\fR for valid units\&.
Default value is "p" as in points\&.
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-pdfa\fR \fIlevel\fR
Enables PDF/A conformance for the document\&.
Valid values are \fB\fR (none, default), \fB1b\fR (PDF/A-1b,
ISO\\u00a019005-1) and \fB2b\fR (PDF/A-2b, ISO\\u00a019005-2)\&.
.sp
When set to \fB1b\fR or \fB2b\fR, pdf4tcl automatically embeds:
.RS
.IP \(bu
An XMP metadata stream with the pdfaid identification schema
(\fIpdfaid:part\fR and \fIpdfaid:conformance\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
An OutputIntent dictionary with an sRGB ICC profile (\fB/GTS_PDFA1\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
Suppresses \fB/Group /S /Transparency\fR on all pages (required
for PDF/A-1)\&.
.RE
.sp
Note: Standard Type\\u00a01 fonts (Helvetica, Times, Courier) are not embedded\&.
For full PDF/A conformance, use CID fonts created with
\fB::pdf4tcl::createFontSpecCID\fR\&.
.sp
Default value is \fB\fR\&.
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-pdfa-icc\fR \fIpath\fR
Explicit path to the sRGB ICC profile file used for the OutputIntent when
\fB-pdfa\fR is \fB1b\fR or \fB2b\fR\&.
.sp
If not specified, pdf4tcl searches for the profile in standard system
locations (e\&.g\&. "\fI/usr/share/color/icc/ghostscript/srgb\&.icc\fR")\&.
.sp
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-userpassword\fR \fIstring\fR
Set a user (open) password for the document\&.
When set, the document cannot be opened without this password\&.
.sp
The encryption level is controlled by \fB-encversion\fR:
AES-128 (default, V=4/R=4) or AES-256 (V=5/R=6)\&.
.sp
Note: \fB-userpassword\fR and \fB-pdfa\fR cannot be combined --
PDF/A forbids encryption (ISO 19005)\&.
.sp
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-ownerpassword\fR \fIstring\fR
Set an owner password for the document\&.
The owner password grants full access regardless of user-password
restrictions\&.
When only \fB-ownerpassword\fR is set (no \fB-userpassword\fR),
the document opens without a password but is protected from modification\&.
.sp
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-encversion\fR \fIinteger\fR
Set the encryption version\&. Must be \fB4\fR (AES-128, default) or
\fB5\fR (AES-256)\&.
.sp
\fB4\fR: AES-128, V=4/R=4, PDF 1\&.5+\&. Pure Tcl, no external programs\&.
.sp
\fB5\fR: AES-256, V=5/R=6, PDF 2\&.0\&. SHA-384/SHA-512 is selected
automatically from three backends in priority order:
\fBtcl-sha\fR (C extension, fastest, optional),
\fBopenssl\fR (if in PATH), or a pure-Tcl fallback (always available,
approx\&. 24 seconds per document)\&. No external program is required\&.
.sp
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.TP
\fB-permissions\fR \fIvalue\fR
Set the access rights for users of an encrypted document\&.
Only meaningful in combination with \fB-userpassword\fR\&.
Accepted values: \fBall\fR (default, /P=-196), \fBnone\fR,
\fBreadonly\fR (print only), a list of flags
(\fBprint\fR, \fBhq-print\fR, \fBmodify\fR, \fBcopy\fR,
\fBannotate\fR, \fBfill-forms\fR, \fBaccessibility\fR,
\fBassemble\fR), or a direct integer /P value\&.
.sp
Note: permissions are enforced by conforming viewers only\&.
The owner password always grants full access\&.
.sp
This option can only be set at object creation\&.
.PP
.SS "PAGE CONFIGURATION"
.TP
\fB-paper\fR \fIname\fR
The argument of this option defines the paper size\&.
The paper size may be a string like "a4", where valid values
are available through \fB::pdf4tcl::getPaperSizeList\fR\&.
Paper size may also be a two element list specifying width and height\&.
.sp
The default value of this option is "a4"\&.
.TP
\fB-landscape\fR \fIboolean\fR
If true, paper width and height are switched\&.
.sp
The default value of this option is false\&.
.TP
\fB-orient\fR \fIboolean\fR
This sets the orientation of the y axis of the coordinate system\&.
With \fB-orient\fR false, origin is in the bottom left corner\&.
With \fB-orient\fR true, origin is in the top left corner\&.
.sp
The default value of this option is true\&.
.TP
\fB-margin\fR \fIvalues\fR
The margin is a one, two or four element list of margins\&.
For one element, it specifies all margins\&.
Two elements specify left/right and top/bottom\&.
Four elements specify left, right, top and bottom\&.
.sp
The default value of this option is zero\&.
.TP
\fB-rotate\fR \fIangle\fR
This value defines a rotation angle for the display of the page\&.
Allowed values are multiples of 90\&.
.sp
The default value of this option is zero\&.
.PP
.SH EXAMPLES
.CS


  pdf4tcl::new mypdf -paper a3
  mypdf startPage
  mypdf setFont 12 Courier
  mypdf text "Hejsan" -x 50 -y 50
  mypdf write -file mypdf\&.pdf
  mypdf destroy

.CE
.SS "UNIT CONVERSION PROCS"
The following procs convert common units to PDF points (1 pt = 1/72 inch)\&.
They can be used directly in any coordinate or distance argument\&.
.TP
\fBpdf4tcl::mm\fR \fIvalue\fR
Convert millimetres to points\&.
.TP
\fBpdf4tcl::cm\fR \fIvalue\fR
Convert centimetres to points\&.
.TP
\fBpdf4tcl::in\fR \fIvalue\fR
Convert inches to points\&.
.TP
\fBpdf4tcl::pt\fR \fIvalue\fR
Identity conversion (returns the value as a floating-point number)\&.
.PP
Example:
.CS


$pdf text "Hello" -x [pdf4tcl::mm 20] -y [pdf4tcl::mm 267]
$pdf roundedRect [pdf4tcl::mm 20] [pdf4tcl::mm 50]                  [pdf4tcl::mm 80] [pdf4tcl::mm 30]                  -radius [pdf4tcl::mm 5] -filled 1

.CE
.SH "PACKAGE VARIABLES"
\fB::pdf4tcl::warnings\fR
A list of non-fatal compliance warnings accumulated during PDF generation\&.
Currently populated by \fBsetAlpha\fR when called with a value less
than 1\&.0 under \fB-pdfa 1b\fR (transparency forbidden by
ISO 19005-1 SS6\&.1\&.3)\&.
.CS


set ::pdf4tcl::warnings {}
set pdf [pdf4tcl::new %AUTO% -pdfa 1b]
$pdf startPage
$pdf setAlpha 0\&.5      ;# appends warning -- no exception raised
$pdf endPage
$pdf destroy
foreach w $::pdf4tcl::warnings { puts "WARNING: $w" }

.CE
Reset before each document with \fBset ::pdf4tcl::warnings {}\fR\&.
The PDF is generated regardless of any warnings in this list\&.
\fB::pdf4tcl::_md5Backend\fR
Set by \fB_InitMD5Backend\fR on first use\&.
Values: \fBtcllib\fR, \fBopenssl\fR, \fBpure-tcl\fR\&.
Read-only; for diagnostics only\&.
.SH CHANGES
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.24"
.PP
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR" (\fBCanvasDoTkoPathItem\fR): Fixed crash when
\fB$path coords $id\fR returns an empty list\&. This happened for
\fBwindow\fR items, \fBgroup\fR items, and items with \fB-matrix\fR
set\&. Added length guard: if coords has fewer than 2 elements, the item
is silently skipped\&. Symptom was \fIcan't read "x1": no such variable\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.24\&.test\fR": 3 new tests -- canvas-4\&.1 (empty
canvas), canvas-4\&.2 (tko::path window item), canvas-4\&.3 (version check)\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.23"
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBgetStringWidth\fR extended with optional
keyword arguments \fB-font\fR and \fB-size\fR (0\&.9\&.4\&.23+)\&.
Text width can now be measured without a prior \fBsetFont\fR call\&.
CIDFont metrics are supported\&. Legacy positional call unchanged\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBinPage\fR added\&. Returns \fB1\fR if a
page is currently open, \fB0\fR otherwise\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBcurrentPage\fR added\&. Returns the current
page number (1-based, \fB0\fR before first \fBstartPage\fR)\&.
\fBpageCount\fR added -- returns the number of completed pages\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBdrawTextBox\fR gains \fB-newyvar\fR
option\&. The named variable receives the Y position after the last rendered
line in the current unit\&. Allows flowing text without manual recalculation\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": Annotation methods added (ISO 32000 SS12\&.5):
\fBaddAnnotNote\fR, \fBaddAnnotFreeText\fR,
\fBaddAnnotHighlight\fR, \fBaddAnnotUnderline\fR,
\fBaddAnnotStrikeOut\fR, \fBaddAnnotStamp\fR, \fBaddAnnotLine\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/cat\&.tcl\fR": \fB::pdf4tcl::exportForms\fR added\&.
Exports form field data from a filled PDF as FDF (ISO 32000 SS12\&.7\&.7)
or XFDF (SS12\&.7\&.8)\&. Returns the number of exported fields\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/options\&.tcl\fR": \fB-pdfa 3b\fR added as valid value\&.
PDF/A-3b allows embedded files with associated file relationships\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBaddEmbeddedFile\fR now tracks FileSpec OIDs
for the document-level \fB/AF\fR array when \fB-pdfa 3b\fR is active\&.
The \fB/AF\fR array in the Catalog associates embedded files with the
document as a whole (ISO 19005-3 SS6\&.2\&.11\&.4)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBaddLayer\fR / \fBbeginLayer\fR:
\fB/AS\fR array added to the OCG \fB/D\fR dictionary when
\fB-pdfa 2b\fR or \fB-pdfa 3b\fR is active (ISO 19005-2 SS6\&.2\&.10)\&.
Defines layer state for Print and View events\&. Standard PDFs and
PDF/A-1b are not affected\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.23-annot\&.test\fR": 20 new tests for
annotation methods (\fBaddAnnotNote\fR, \fBaddAnnotFreeText\fR,
\fBaddAnnotHighlight\fR, \fBaddAnnotUnderline\fR,
\fBaddAnnotStrikeOut\fR, \fBaddAnnotStamp\fR, \fBaddAnnotLine\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.23\&.test\fR": 23 new tests --
\fB-pdfa 3b\fR validation (3), \fB/AF\fR array (4),
\fB/AS\fR array (5), \fBgetStringWidth\fR with \fB-font\fR/\fB-size\fR (3),
\fBinPage\fR / \fBcurrentPage\fR / \fBpageCount\fR (5),
\fBdrawTextBox\fR \fB-newyvar\fR (2), \fB::pdf4tcl::exportForms\fR (5)\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.22"
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": PDF/A-2b now writes a cross-reference stream
(\fB_WriteXrefStream\fR) instead of a classic xref table\&.
Required by ISO 19005-2 SS6\&.1\&.4\&. PDF/A-1b continues to use the classic
table (XRef streams forbidden by ISO 19005-1 SS6\&.1\&.3)\&.
Classic xref table extracted into \fB_WriteXrefTable\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": PDF version set to 1\&.7 for \fB-pdfa 2b\fR
(ISO 19005-2 SS4\&.1 requires PDF 1\&.7 as base format)\&.
PDF/A-1b and standard PDFs remain at PDF 1\&.4\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBsetAlpha\fR with a value less than 1\&.0
under \fB-pdfa 1b\fR appends a warning to \fB::pdf4tcl::warnings\fR
(transparency forbidden by ISO 19005-1 SS6\&.1\&.3)\&.
No exception is raised -- the PDF is generated regardless\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/prologue\&.tcl\fR": \fB::pdf4tcl::warnings\fR list added\&.
Accumulates non-fatal compliance warnings\&. Check after document creation;
reset with \fBset ::pdf4tcl::warnings {}\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/encrypt\&.tcl\fR": MD5 backend chain added (\fB_InitMD5Backend\fR,
\fB_MD5\fR, \fB_MD5Init\fR, \fB_MD5Update\fR, \fB_MD5Final\fR,
\fB_MD5PureTcl\fR)\&.
Priority: Tcllib md5 -> openssl -> pure-Tcl implementation (RFC 1321)\&.
AES-128 encryption now works on FIPS systems without Tcllib\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.22\&.test\fR": 17 new tests --
XRef-Stream (7), PDF version (3), setAlpha warning (2), MD5 pure-Tcl (5)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIdemo/demo-pdfa\&.tcl\fR": New page 4 documenting XRef-Stream
structure, PDF/A-2b implementation, and 0\&.9\&.4\&.22 fixes\&.
PDF version on page 1 now dynamically reflects actual document version\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIdemo/demo-alpha\&.tcl\fR": New section 8 showing the
\fB-pdfa 1b\fR + \fBsetAlpha\fR warning mechanism\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.21"
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": ICC profile stream compressed with
\fBFlateDecode\fR when \fB-compress\fR is active\&.
Previously written as raw uncompressed stream\&.
Saves approximately 2 KB per PDF/A document\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": New public methods \fBaddLayer\fR,
\fBbeginLayer\fR, \fBendLayer\fR implement Optional Content Groups
(OCG / Layers, ISO 32000 SS8\&.11)\&.
Supports debug grids, letterhead variants, watermarks\&.
Layer visibility controlled by \fB-visible\fR (default: 1)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/nist\&.test\fR": NIST SHA/AES reference vectors now run
as part of \fBmake test\fR via a tcltest wrapper\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.21\&.test\fR": 13 new tests --
ICC compression (5) and OCG/Layer (8)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIdemo/demo-layers\&.tcl\fR": New 3-page demo for OCG/Layer\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.20"
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": New public methods \fBtransform\fR,
\fBrotate\fR, \fBscale\fR, \fBtranslate\fR apply PDF coordinate
transformations\&. Drawing commands work correctly in the transformed
system via the new \fBrawcoords\fR graphics state flag
(saved/restored by \fBgsave\fR/\fBgrestore\fR)\&.
\fBtransform\fR, \fBrotate\fR, \fBscale\fR, \fBtranslate\fR
call \fBEndTextObj\fR before emitting the \fBcm\fR operator\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": New method \fBgetPageSize\fR returns the
full page dimensions as \fB{width height}\fR in the current unit\&.
Complements \fBgetDrawableArea\fR (which excludes margins)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": New option \fB-permissions\fR controls
the access rights (\fB/P\fR value) for encrypted PDFs\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItools/bump\&.tcl\fR": Version-bump tool consolidated\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIexamples/test-transform\&.tcl\fR": New example for
\fBtranslate\fR, \fBrotate\fR, \fBscale\fR, \fBgetPageSize\fR\&.
Added to "\fItests/examples\&.test\fR" as \fBexamples-1\&.7\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.20\&.test\fR": 23 tests covering
\fBgetPageSize\fR, \fBtransform\fR, \fBrotate\fR, \fBscale\fR,
\fBtranslate\fR, and \fBrawcoords\fR state management\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.19"
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": XMP stream is now accumulated as UTF-8 bytes
(\fBencoding convertto utf-8\fR before \fBPdfout\fR)\&. Fixes
EILSEQ when \fBmetadata\fR \fB-title\fR contains codepoints
above U+00FF under Tcl 9\&. Resolves knownbug cidfont-9\&.2\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/cidfont\&.test\fR": knownbug constraint removed from
cidfont-9\&.2\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.18\&.test\fR": 24 new tests covering
\fBwrite\fR, \fB_ValidatePdfDate\fR, \fBCleanText\fR,
metadata Unicode handling, and \fB::pdf4tcl::sha2pure\fR
NIST vectors\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.18"
.IP \(bu
Tcl 9 compatibility: pdf4tcl runs under both Tcl 8\&.6 and Tcl 9\&.0\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/encrypt\&.tcl\fR": \fB_InitSHABackend\fR selects the correct
SHA library path under Tcl 9\&. SHA output uses hex encoding and
\fBbinary decode hex\fR for binary-safe results on all platforms\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/encrypt\&.tcl\fR": New methods \fB_AesCbc\fR and
\fB_AesEcb\fR wrap all \fBaes::aes\fR calls with
\fBbinary format a*\fR to guarantee bytearrays under Tcl 8\&.6 and Tcl 9\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/helpers\&.tcl\fR": \fBCleanText\fR handles non-convertible
characters one by one using \fBcatch\fR -- Tcl 9 throws instead of
substituting\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fBwrite\fR sets \fB-encoding iso8859-1\fR
in addition to \fB-translation binary\fR to prevent EILSEQ errors
under Tcl 9\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": \fB_ValidatePdfDate\fR checks Unix timestamp
range (below 10^12) -- Tcl 9 accepts arbitrarily large integers in
\fBstring is integer\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
Makefile: \fBTCLSH ?=\fR allows override via environment\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/util\&.test\fR": \fB-translation binary\fR replaces
\fB-encoding binary\fR (removed in Tcl 9)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/examples\&.test\fR": example PDFs are auto-regenerated when
the Tcl version changes ("\fI\&.tclver\fR" fingerprint file)\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItests/cidfont\&.test\fR": test cidfont-9\&.2 marked as knownbug\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fItools/tcl9env\&.sh\fR": new file -- sets Tcl 9 environment for
\fBmake test\fR and \fBmake example\fR\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.17"
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/encrypt\&.tcl\fR": AES-256 string encryption
(\fBEncryptStringsInBody\fR, \fB_PdfLiteralToBytes\fR) wired into
four call sites in "\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": FlushObjects, radio group parent,
info dictionary, and bookmarks\&. Fixes AcroForm field corruption in
encrypted documents\&.
.IP \(bu
"\fIsrc/encrypt\&.tcl\fR": SHA-384/512 pure-Tcl implementation
(\fB::pdf4tcl::sha2pure\fR, NIST FIPS 180-4 compliant)\&. AES-256
no longer requires any external program\&.
.IP \(bu
SHA backend priority: \fBtcl-sha\fR (C extension) >
\fBopenssl\fR (if in PATH) > pure-Tcl fallback (always available)\&.
.IP \(bu
Combobox and listbox generate their own appearance streams\&.
\fBNeedAppearances\fR is never set; all field types coexist correctly
with signature fields\&.
.IP \(bu
New options \fB-required\fR and \fB-label\fR in
\fBaddForm\fR\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.16"
.IP \(bu
AES-256 encryption (V=5, R=6, PDF 2\&.0, ISO 32000-2 §7\&.6\&.4)\&.
New option \fB-encversion\fR: \fB4\fR (AES-128, default) or
\fB5\fR (AES-256)\&. SHA-384/512 via openssl subprocess (superseded
by pure-Tcl fallback in 0\&.9\&.4\&.17)\&.
Algorithm 2\&.B implemented after pypdf/qpdf reference
("\fIlibqpdf/QPDF_encryption\&.cc\fR")\&.
.IP \(bu
Fixed "\fIsrc/main\&.tcl\fR": Makefile dependency
"\fIweb/mypdf\&.pdf\fR" now depends on "\fIpdf4tcl\&.tcl\fR" to ensure
correct build order\&.
.IP \(bu
Extended "\fItests/encrypt\&.test\fR" with 12 AES-256 tests
(encrypt-9\&.1 through encrypt-9\&.12)\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.13"
.IP \(bu
New method \fBsetBlendMode\fR: sets the PDF blend mode for
subsequent graphics operations via ExtGState \fB/BM\fR\&. Supported modes:
\fBNormal\fR, \fBMultiply\fR, \fBScreen\fR, \fBOverlay\fR,
\fBDarken\fR, \fBLighten\fR, \fBColorDodge\fR, \fBColorBurn\fR,
\fBHardLight\fR, \fBSoftLight\fR, \fBDifference\fR, \fBExclusion\fR,
\fBHue\fR, \fBSaturation\fR, \fBColor\fR, \fBLuminosity\fR\&.
Requires PDF 1\&.4 (version is raised automatically)\&. ExtGState objects are
cached per mode + alpha combination\&.
.IP \(bu
New method \fBgetBlendMode\fR: returns the currently active blend
mode (default \fBNormal\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
New method \fBlinearGradient\fR: paints a linear (axial) gradient
between two points using PDF ShadingType 2 + FunctionType 2\&. Options:
\fB-extend\fR \fIbool bool\fR (default \fB1 1\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
New method \fBradialGradient\fR: paints a radial gradient between
two circles using PDF ShadingType 3 + FunctionType 2\&. Options:
\fB-extend\fR \fIbool bool\fR (default \fB1 1\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
New internal helper \fB_colorToRGB\fR: accepts an RGB triple
\fI{r g b}\fR, a named color (\fBred\fR, \fBgreen\fR, \fBblue\fR,
\fBwhite\fR, \fBblack\fR, \fByellow\fR, \fBcyan\fR, \fBmagenta\fR)
or a CSS hex string \fI#rrggbb\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
New options \fB-tooltip\fR and \fB-tabindex\fR in
\fBaddForm\fR: \fB-tooltip\fR writes \fB/TU\fR (PDF/UA accessible
tooltip); \fB-tabindex\fR writes \fB/TI\fR (tab order index within
AcroForm, non-negative integer)\&.
.IP \(bu
\fBendPage\fR now writes \fB/Tabs /R\fR into the page
dictionary when annotations are present, enabling correct tab order for
screen readers\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.12"
.IP \(bu
New method \fBroundedRect\fR: draws a rectangle with rounded
corners using Bezier approximation\&. Options \fB-radius\fR (default 5),
\fB-filled\fR, \fB-stroke\fR\&. Radius is automatically clamped to
half the shorter side\&.
.IP \(bu
New namespace procs \fBpdf4tcl::mm\fR, \fBpdf4tcl::cm\fR,
\fBpdf4tcl::in\fR, \fBpdf4tcl::pt\fR: convert common units to PDF points
(1 pt = 1/72 inch)\&. Use directly in coordinate arguments\&.
.IP \(bu
Date validation in \fBmetadata\fR: new method
\fB_ValidatePdfDate\fR validates and normalises PDF date strings for
\fB-creationdate\fR and \fB-moddate\fR\&. Throws \fBPDF4TCL BADDATE\fR
on invalid format\&.
.IP \(bu
Extended "\fI0\&.9\&.4\&.x/demo/demo-alpha\&.tcl\fR" with sections
demonstrating \fBroundedRect\fR and unit conversion procs\&.
.IP \(bu
New test file "\fItests/new-0\&.9\&.4\&.12\&.test\fR": 17 tests\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.11"
.IP \(bu
New module "\fIsrc/encrypt\&.tcl\fR": AES-128 encryption (V=4, R=4)
per PDF 1\&.6 specification\&. New options \fB-userpassword\fR and
\fB-ownerpassword\fR\&. The Encrypt dictionary uses
\fB/CFM\fR \fB/AESV2\fR, \fB/StmF\fR \fB/StdCF\fR,
\fB/StrF\fR \fB/StdCF\fR\&. Padding constant corrected
to 0x7A (qpdf-compatible)\&.
.IP \(bu
Extended \fB_FindSRGBProfile\fR with TeX Live path variants for
the sRGB ICC profile (glob search for year-variable path components)\&.
.IP \(bu
New test file "\fItests/encrypt\&.test\fR": 25 tests covering
AES-128 encryption, O/U-entry calculation, and Encrypt dictionary
structure\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.10"
.IP \(bu
Added \fBsetAlpha\fR: sets fill and/or stroke opacity (0\&.0 transparent,
1\&.0 opaque) via PDF ExtGState (/ca, /CA)\&. Supports single value, \fB-fill\fR,
\fB-stroke\fR, and two-value form for independent fill/stroke control\&.
.IP \(bu
Added \fBgetAlpha\fR: returns current fill and stroke opacity as a list\&.
.IP \(bu
Alpha state is saved and restored by \fBgsave\fR / \fBgrestore\fR\&.
.IP \(bu
ExtGState objects are cached: identical alpha values reuse one PDF object\&.
.IP \(bu
Added \fBdemo-alpha\&.tcl\fR: demonstrates transparency with overlapping shapes,
alpha steps, independent fill/stroke alpha, transparent text, and gsave/grestore\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.9"
.IP \(bu
Added \fBdemo-pdfa\&.tcl\fR: Demonstration of PDF/A-1b and PDF/A-2b features
using embedded CIDFont (DejaVuSans)\&. Requires no Ghostscript\&.
.IP \(bu
Added \fBdemo-pdfa-gs\&.tcl\fR: PDF/A conversion workflow via Ghostscript\&.
Produces PDF/A-1b and PDF/A-2b from a pdf4tcl source document\&.
.IP \(bu
Extended \fBdemo-all\&.tcl\fR with page 6 (section 12): PDF/A feature overview,
usage example, 1b vs\&. 2b comparison table, and font embedding requirement\&.
.IP \(bu
Added \fBSafeQuoteString\fR tests ("\fItests/util\&.test\fR" util-9\&.1\&.\&.9\&.5):
covers ASCII passthrough, Latin-1 retention, SMP replacement, PDF special
character escaping, and mixed input\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.8"
.IP \(bu
PDF/A-1b and PDF/A-2b support via \fB-pdfa\fR option\&.
.IP \(bu
XMP metadata stream with pdfaid identification schema
(\fIpdfaid:part\fR, \fIpdfaid:conformance\fR)\&.
.IP \(bu
OutputIntent with sRGB ICC profile (\fB-pdfa-icc\fR for explicit path)\&.
.IP \(bu
\fI/Group/S/Transparency\fR suppressed for PDF/A-1 pages\&.
.IP \(bu
Binary comment (4 bytes > 0x7F) in PDF header\&.
.IP \(bu
Fixed \fI/Length\fR calculation to use UTF-8 byte count\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.7"
.IP \(bu
Assembled "\fIpdf4tcl\&.tcl\fR", updated examples, manpage and tests\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.6"
.IP \(bu
Added \fBSafeQuoteString\fR: strips codepoints > U+00FF before PDF encoding
for Tcl 9\&.0 compatibility (ticket #17)\&.
.IP \(bu
Fixed CID \fI\&.notdef\fR width handling\&.
.IP \(bu
Improved \fBGetCharWidth\fR fallback for unmappable WinAnsi codepoints\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.5"
.IP \(bu
CIDFont Unicode support: \fBcreateFontSpecCID\fR for full TTF embedding\&.
.IP \(bu
Supports Latin Extended, Greek, Cyrillic, CJK and all BMP/SMP codepoints\&.
.IP \(bu
ToUnicode CMap with UTF-16BE surrogate pairs for SMP characters\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.3"
.IP \(bu
Added \fBhyperlinkAdd\fR: URI annotation links with optional border and color
(ticket #15)\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.1"
.IP \(bu
AcroForm v2\&.1: extended \fBaddForm\fR from 2 to 8 field types: \fItext\fR,
\fIpassword\fR, \fIcheckbutton\fR, \fIcombobox\fR, \fIlistbox\fR,
\fIradiobutton\fR, \fIpushbutton\fR, \fIsignature\fR\&.
Added \fB-required\fR, \fB-label\fR and radio group support (ticket #9)\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.15"
.IP \(bu
OTF/CFF font support in \fBpdf4tcl::loadBaseTrueTypeFont\fR:
OpenType fonts with CFF outlines ("\fI\&.otf\fR" files, OTTO magic number
\fB0x4F54544F\fR) are now accepted without error\&.
Previously these fonts caused \fITTF: postscript outlines are not supported\fR\&.
.sp
No CFF parser is required: pdf4tcl embeds the font binary as-is and reads
only metadata tables (\fBname\fR, \fBhead\fR, \fBOS/2\fR,
\fBpost\fR, \fBhhea\fR, \fBmaxp\fR, \fBcmap\fR, \fBhmtx\fR)\&.
\fBloca\fR and \fBglyf\fR tables (TTF-only) are skipped for CFF fonts\&.
.sp
PDF embedding uses \fB/CIDFontType0\fR with \fB/FontFile3\fR
(\fB/Subtype /OpenType\fR) instead of the TTF path
(\fB/CIDFontType2\fR / \fB/FontFile2\fR / \fB/Length1\fR)\&.
The ToUnicode CMap and all other font objects are identical\&.
.sp
A new internal flag \fBBFA($name,isCFF)\fR is set to \fB1\fR for
CFF/OTF fonts and \fB0\fR for TrueType fonts\&.
.PP
.SS "VERSION 0\&.9\&.4\&.14"
.IP \(bu
New method \fBaddEmbeddedFile\fR: embeds a file silently into the
PDF Catalog \fB/Names\fR / \fB/EmbeddedFiles\fR NameTree
(ISO 32000 SS7\&.11\&.4)\&. No visible page annotation is created\&.
Options: \fB-contents\fR (raw data), \fB-mimetype\fR,
\fB-description\fR, \fB-afrelationship\fR
(\fBAlternative\fR | \fBData\fR | \fBSource\fR |
\fBSupplement\fR | \fBUnspecified\fR)\&.
Calling this method when \fB-pdfa\fR is \fB1b\fR raises an error
(ISO 19005-1 SS6\&.1\&.7)\&. Intended use: ZUGFeRD / Factur-X electronic
invoices and other document-level attachments\&.
.PP
